Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light pink-brown; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Secondary stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '190', circled. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200,1a? Name Aristogenes. Perhaps from the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 068.16.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1107)
